        public MutableString copyFrom(MutableString other)
        Copies the contents of another MutableString.

      • toUpperCase

        public MutableString toUpperCase(MutableStringFactory factory)
        Returns a copy of this string with all ASCII lower case characters converted to upper case, or returns this if it contains no ASCII lower case characters.

        Only ASCII characters from a-z are converted.

        Parameters:
        factory - factory from which a new MutableString is created, if necessary
        Returns:
        a copy of this string with all ASCII lower case characters converted to upper case, or this if it contains no ASCII lower case characters

        public void recycle()
        Description copied from interface: Recyclable
        Recycle the object.

        It is up to the concrete implementation to define precisely what being recycled means, however, the caller is entitled to assume that all internal state is cleared and that the object behaves in exactly the same way as it did on initial usage.
